OL,3,GOPINIONCReflections on this week's
OL,4,Cplayout incident on BBC Scotland
OL,5,
OL,6,FIn the old days, TV went wrong far more
OL,7,Foften than it does today.
OL,9,FProgrammes on film and VT broke down
OL,10,Fwhen machines developed problems.
OL,12,FLive programmes could suffer from all
OL,13,Fsorts of issues.
OL,15,FOutside broadcasts were also prone to
OL,16,Fall kinds of failings ` from the link
OL,17,Fto the studio going down to the fire
OL,18,Fbell going off at a venue.
OL,20,FBut for BBC viewers at least, these
OL,21,Fproblems rarely led to on-air
OL,22,Fcatastrophes.
OL,23,EPub: 22-Mar-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,147,140,200,120,0,100
