OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F146A1776604038
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/9
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCReflections on this week's
OL,4,Cplayout incident on BBC Scotland
OL,5,
OL,6,FIn the nations at least, the local
OL,7,Fpresentation departments were usually
OL,8,Fon the case within seconds.
OL,10,FIndeed dealing with these situations
OL,11,Fwas an Important part of the
OL,12,Fannouncer's job.
OL,14,FFormer senior announcer Richard Straker
OL,15,Fexplained it during a 1987 edition of
OL,16,FOpen Air when a viewer wondered if they
OL,17,Fmight start appearing in-vision like
OL,18,Fthe CBBC presenters.
OL,23,EPub: 22-Mar-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,147,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14604
SC,0004
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F146A1776604038
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G4/9
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCReflections on this week's
OL,4,Cplayout incident on BBC Scotland
OL,5,
OL,6,FIndeed I wonder how often Richard and
OL,7,Fhis colleagues sounded like they were
OL,8,Fcalmly keeping the show on the road
OL,9,Fwhile their colleagues in NC1 and NC2
OL,10,Fwere frantically trying to sort out
OL,11,Fmajor problems.
OL,13,FOf course, it was the moments like
OL,14,Fthese which those of us who enjoyed
OL,15,FPresentation in our younger days
OL,16,Fcherished.
OL,18,FBut these moments also told us so much
OL,19,Fabout the professionalism of BBC
OL,20,FPresentation and the resilience
OL,21,Farrangements.
OL,23,EPub: 22-Mar-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,147,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14605
SC,0005
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F146A1776604038
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G5/9
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCReflections on this week's
OL,4,Cplayout incident on BBC Scotland
OL,5,
OL,6,FContinuity was the first line of
OL,7,Fdefence in a disaster. Continuity made
OL,8,Fsure that breakdowns ` which were then
OL,9,Fmuch more frequent than today ` did not
OL,10,Fcompromise the integrity of the BBC.
OL,12,FI highlight all of this because of last
OL,13,Fweek's disaster in Scotland during the
OL,14,Ffirst few minutes of the BBC News at
OL,15,FSix.
OL,17,FIt is not for us to speculate on just
OL,18,Fhow this catastrophe occurred or say
OL,19,Fwho was or was not responsible.
OL,23,EPub: 22-Mar-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,147,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14606
SC,0006
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F146A1776604038
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G6/9
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCReflections on this week's
OL,4,Cplayout incident on BBC Scotland
OL,5,
OL,6,FBut I would suggest the BBC needs to
OL,7,Fthink carefully about resilience
OL,8,Farrangements more generally up and down
OL,9,Fthe country.
OL,11,FThere have been too many examples in
OL,12,Frecent years of problems and breakdowns
OL,13,Fbecoming catastrophes. I still shudder
OL,14,Fat the night an edition of Panorama
OL,15,Fwent wrong.
OL,17,FI would suggest a few basic steps might
OL,18,Fbe considered.
OL,23,EPub: 22-Mar-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,147,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14607
SC,0007
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F146A1776604038
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G7/9
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCReflections on this week's
OL,4,Cplayout incident on BBC Scotland
OL,5,
OL,6,FFirstly it should always be possible to
OL,7,Fcut to a breakdown caption within
OL,8,Fseconds. There should never be a blank
OL,9,Fscreen or the "wrong" material.
OL,11,FSecondly we need announcers who can
OL,12,Fcalmly apologise without stumbling `
OL,13,Feven when their heart is beating
OL,14,Ffaster.
OL,16,FThirdly, should announcers be required
OL,17,Fto play some appropriate music like
OL,18,Fthey used to? To my mind, the looped
OL,19,Fambient sound which accompanies the
OL,20,Fbreakdown caption makes things worse.
OL,23,EPub: 22-Mar-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,147,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14608
SC,0008
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F146A1776604038
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G8/9
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCReflections on this week's
OL,4,Cplayout incident on BBC Scotland
OL,5,
OL,6,FA few other questions are worth
OL,7,Fexploring.
OL,9,FIn general, might some network
OL,10,Fdirectors and announcers lack
OL,11,Fsufficient experience in dealing with
OL,12,Femergencies? This can be put right with
OL,13,Ftraining and realistic exercises in
OL,14,Fdealing with all the likely scenarios.
OL,16,FPerhaps part of the discussion might
OL,17,Finvolve asking whether network
OL,18,Fpresentation should be brought back
OL,19,Fin-house when Red Bee's contract
OL,20,Fexpires.
OL,23,EPub: 22-Mar-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,147,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14609
SC,0009
